					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well here they are:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/NotesTableNTSC.txt">http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/NotesTableNTSC.txt</a><!-- m -->
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/NotesTablePAL.txt">http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/NotesTablePAL.txt</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />You really wouldn't get this precision for the PAL table if you just used the NTSC table plus 1 <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> .
<br />
<br />I've tested all the values. They're all good except after about halfway through octave 7 every pitch is so high you can't really tell what you're hearing (if you could though, it'd be right I'm sure).
<br />
<br />Hope this is useful.
<br />
<br />Also, Bregalad, multiplying by 15/16 seems to give fairly close results, but they weren't the same answers that I got when I used the equation. For example, Multiplying $7F1 by 15/16 gave me $771, when the equation gave me $760.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

