					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So to get the most possible precision using the "one octave table and shift" method I would have to do the following.
<br />
<br />Generate a LUT for the lowest octave (octave 0) using 1662607/(f*16) where f is the frequecy of the notes.
<br />
<br />And then the following in the playback code.
<br />
<br />get period from LUT
<br />divide period by 2^octave (correctly rounded)
<br />subtract 1
<br />
<br />Will this give maximum possible precision?
<br />
<br />EDIT:
<br />I live in PAL land.</div>

